large mount studies use regression models identify influencing factors evaluate effect size. Previous research demonstrated single factor determining travel behavior. choosing continues response, like Vehicle Miles Traveled (VMT),3 basic structure regression model :\[\begin{equation}
\mathbf{y}=\mathbf{X}\boldsymbol{\beta}+\boldsymbol{\varepsilon}
\tag{1.1}
\end{equation}\]\(\mathbf{Y}\) variable VMT. \(\mathbf{X}\) relevant covariates corresponding coefficients \(\boldsymbol{\beta}\). \(\boldsymbol{\varepsilon}\) random error terms expected value \(0\) variance \(\sigma^2\).response categorical variable, binary data driving versus , polytomous data mode choice, count data trip frequency, proper model :\[\begin{equation}
