\tag{1.2}
\end{equation}\]\(E[\mathbf{Y}|\mathbf{X}]\) expected value individual/household-level travel variable \(\mathbf{Y}\) conditional \(\mathbf{X}\); \(\mathbf{X}\boldsymbol{\beta}\) linear combination (Ditto.); \(g(\cdot)\) link function.

Law MigrationAn early theory called Law Migration Ravenstein (1885) tried explain regional migration patterns. found based observation rather quantitative analysis. capture fact direction migration toward regional center great commerce industry. also pointed distance primary factor migrant. theory inspired many studies population movement consequently. Even today, socio-economic factors distance-constraints essential parts relevant models frameworks.Zipf’s LawZip’s law also called discrete Pareto distribution. found linguistics explain inverse relationship frequency rank word. charm rank-frequency distribution disclosed universal law many realms society physics, urban size, corporation sizes, cells’ transcriptomes . Zipf interpreted two competing factors force diversification unification. former produces larger amount cases later tries upgrade rank. equilibrium rank-frequency balance controlled parameter \(\alpha\) exponent. example, city’s population size \(m\) negative power relationship rank \(r\) .11\[
m \sim 1 / r^{\alpha}
\]Zipf (1946) extended expression describe traffic directions two cities:\[
t_{ij}\propto \frac{m_i m_j} {d_{ij}}
 \]\(t_{ij}\) represent traffic flow goods two centers \(\) \(j\) population sizes \(m_i\) \(m_j\). \(d_{ij}\) distance \(\) \(j\). Zipf’s formula form Newtonian mechanics (Newton 1848), people call expression Gravity Law.Gravity LawAs influential theory, Gravity Law asserts amount traffic flow two centers proportional product mass inverse distance. mass often measured population size.\[\begin{equation}
p_{ij}\propto m_i m_j f(d_{ij}), \qquad \ne j 
\tag{3.1}
\end{equation}\]\(p_{ij}\) probability commuting origin \(\) destination \(j\), satisfying \(\sum_{,j=1}^n p_{ij}=1\). \(m_i\) \(m_j\) population two census units. travel cost two places represented distance decay function \(d_{ij}\) .Exponential power two forms distance decay function parameter \(\lambda\) showed :\[
f(d_{ij})=\exp(-\lambda d_{ij})
\] \[
f(d_{ij})={d_{ij}}^{-\lambda}
\] function implies movements origin destination decays distance. transportation modeling, common form gravity model :\[
T_{ij}= \alpha_i O_i \cdot \beta_j D_j \cdot f(d_{ij})
\]\(T_{ij}\) flow \(\) \(j\). two population replaced total tirp generation origin \(O_i\) total trip attraction destination \(D_i\). \(\alpha_i\) \(\beta_j\) two constraining parameters satisfy \(\sum_{}^{n_i}T_{ij} = D_j\) \(\sum_{j}^{n_j}T_{ij} = O_i\). means \(\alpha_i = [\sum_{j}^{n_j} \beta_j D_j \cdot f(d_{ij})]^{-1}\) \(\beta_j = [\sum_{}^{n_i} \alpha_i O_i \cdot f(d_{ij})]^{-1}\). Thus, model called doubly constrained gravity model.relieves two constrains. model simplified single-constrained unconstrained gravity model. assuming \(\alpha\beta\) adjustment parameter irrelevant locations \(\) \(j\) controlling total flows, model guarantee attraction destination equals sum flow origins, generation origin equals sum flow destinations.Power LawBroadly speaking, Zipf’s law Gravity Law common essence power law, scaling pattern. Zipfian distribution one family power-law probability distributions. power-law distribution also holds many realms: urban size, population density, street blocks, building heights, etc.state---art studies human mobility agree travel behavior follows power-law distribution population level (Barbosa et al. 2018). example Brockmann, Hufnagel, Geisel (2006) use dollar bills track travel habits confirm theory. reflects fact trip land use, two geographic variables, follow Paretian-like distribution. Apparently, conflicts Gaussian thinking, foundation frame linear models based location scale parameters.12Meanwhile, log-normal distribution may asymptotically equivalent special case Zipf’s law, support logarithm transform current VMT-density models (Saichev, Malevergne, Sornette 2010).

Law Intervening OpportunitiesLaw Intervening Opportunities Stouffer (1940) developed migration theory different direction. Stouffer proposed “number people going given distance directly proportional number opportunities distance inversely proportional number intervening opportunities.”Comparing gravity law, number intervening opportunities \(s_{ij}\) replaces distance origin destination. example, resident living location \(\) attracted location \(j\) \(s_{ij}\) job opportunities .\[
p_{ij}\propto m_i \frac{P(1|m_i,m_j,s_{ij})}{\sum_{k=1}^n P(1|m_i,m_j,s_{ij})}, \qquad \ne j 
\]conditional probability \(P(1|m_i,m_j,s_{ij})\) can expressed Schneider (1959) :\[
