\]transportation model expressed :\[
T_{ij}= O_i\cdot\frac{m_i m_j}{(m_i + s_{ij})(m_i + m_j + s_{ij})}
\] approximating number opportunities, \(s_{ij}\) population within circle centered origin. radius distance \(\) \(j\). \(m_i + m_j + s_{ij}\) represents total population within circle, \(m_i + s_{ij}\) total population within circle excluding \(j\), :\[
T_{ij}= O_i\cdot\frac{m_i }{m_i + s_{ij}}\cdot\frac{m_j}{m_i + m_j + s_{ij}}
\] part fraction converts product two weights, weights origin destination whole region. Although distance \(d_{ij}\) doesn’t appear expression radiation model, still determinant gravity model.Distance Decay (hazard models)Using survival analysis framework, Yang et al. (2014) extended model assuming trip origin destination time--event process. time variable replaced number opportunities.survival function \(S(t)=Pr(T>t)\) represents cumulative probability event happened within certain amount opportunities. Choosing Weibull distribution survival function, \(S(t)=\exp[-\lambda t^\alpha]\) scale parameter \(\lambda \(0, +\infty)\). assuming \(f(\lambda)=\exp[-\lambda]\) integral \(\lambda\), derivation :replacing \(t\) \(m_i+s_{ij}\), conditional probability :\[
\begin{aligned}
P(1|m_i,m_j,s_{ij})= &\frac{P(T>m_i+s_{ij})-P(T> m_i+s_{ij}+m_j)}{P(T>m_i)} \\ 
=&\frac{[(m_i + s_{ij} + m_j)^{\alpha}-(m_i + s_{ij})^{\alpha}](m_i^{\alpha}+1)}{[(m_i + s_{ij} + m_j)^{\alpha}+1][(m_i + s_{ij})^{\alpha}+1]}\\
\end{aligned}
\]\(\alpha\) parameter adjusting effect number job opportunities origins destinations.similar method can found Ding, Mishra, et al. (2017) ’s study. use multilevel hazard model examine effects TAZ level individual level factors respect commuting distance using data Washington metropolitan area.Based commuting data six countries, Lenormand, Bassolas, Ramasco (2016) found gravity law performs better intervening opportunities law. reasons circle radius \(d_{ij}\) can accurately represent real influencing area, different population opportunities captured way.

